# Build output in the conformance FIXTURE tree — CP7R5-K4-IGNORE.
#
# Companion to profiles/.gitignore; see that file for the full rationale. The failure mode here is
# the second of the two the per-item pattern suffers: fixtures are never pruned, but each fixture's
# ignore rules live in ITS OWN scaffold/.gitignore, so a NEWLY ADDED fixture directory arrives with
# no coverage at all until someone remembers to add one. This file covers the whole tree, so a new
# fixture is protected by construction.
#
# Current exposure is low and this is mostly durable insurance: measured at authoring time, ZERO
# directories under conformance/fixtures/ carry a build manifest (no package.json, no *.csproj), so
# no toolchain runs here today. That can change the moment a fixture gains one.
#
# THIS DOES NOT AFFECT YOUR APPLICATION SOURCE — it applies only inside conformance/fixtures/.
#
# Enforced by conformance/build-output-ignored.sh.

# .NET
bin/
obj/
publish/
TestResults/

# JVM
target/
build/
.gradle/

# Python
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
*.egg-info/
.venv/
.coverage

# Node / TypeScript
node_modules/
dist/
coverage/

# Go
cover.out

# .NET coverage artifact (coverlet)
coverage.json
